	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=116639"><span id=" ">Lady SnowBanx</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">203 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.43]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Warrior doesn't need 2 pure hate proc weapons, but the raid does have to make adjustments if the warrior doesn't. Incite is supposed to be 400 hate, this 288dd+stun is prolly more then that. And even if a 700 hate proc'ing weapon did go off initiall it don't mean you'll still have agro. The person with this weapon could have proc'd twice or three times, heck I've proc'd this specific weapon 6 times almost within a minute. In 3-4 minutes it's possible you wont proc at all which I'm certain has happened on more then a few occations. Remember, 1 persons chance against 30 people isn't good. Why deal with these odds. Wear weapons with damage procs, not dd+stuns. I can't remember but I think with this in main hand and my other 180dd+stun the pure damage off the procs were about 18dps, but if ya wanna do the math using the avg proc rate it would be about 2x288/60=9.6 total dps on procs. Chances are you can get this, you can get a simular ratio weapon (or better) with a proc of about 150 or so. 2x150/60=5, so what if it's lesser, at least you wont be causing problems.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
